I can configure my socket.io server to match what the arduino is sending I just don't understand how the events are handled on the arduino. for example when I send a message from my frontend to the socket server I can configure it this way on the socket server:
```
  socket.on("message", (data) => {
    console.log("message received");
  })
```
so `"message"` is my topic/event right? how do I dictate the topic on the arduino?

```
void loop() {
  if (!webSocket.connected()) {
    webSocket.begin("ws://your_server_url_here");
  }

  webSocket.loop();

  // Create a JSON object and send it to the server
  String jsonString = "{\"temperature\": 25, \"humidity\": 50}";
  webSocket.send(jsonString);
}
```
this is a loop chatgpt constructed for me. when I'd send this kind of data to the socket server what "event" does it expect?
